  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple layers of regulations and laws:\n\n1. International Level\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act in the United States\n- Proceeds of Crime Act in the UK\n- Comprehensive legal statutes defining money laundering offenses\n\n3. Key Regulatory Components\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n\n4. Criminal Penalties\n- Significant financial penalties\n- Potential imprisonment\n- Asset seizure\n- Corporate and individual accountability\n\n5. Prevention Mechanisms\n- Mandatory reporting by financial institutions\n- Enhanced background checks\n- International information sharing\n- Risk-based compliance frameworks\n\n6. Enforcement Agencies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Regulatory bodies\n- Specialized investigative departments\n\nThe framework aims to detect, prevent, and prosecute financial crimes while maintaining economic transparency and integrity.",
